<item>
            <title>[CXF-2916] unmarshalling the JSON of a subclass fails when a field value is null</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-2916</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Unmarshalling the JSON :&lt;/p&gt;

{&quot;@xsi.type&quot; : &quot;subClassTest&quot;, &quot;id&quot; : &quot;10000000&quot;, &quot;name&quot; : null }

&lt;p&gt;should give an instance of SubClassTest.class and the value of the field name(which is a String) should be null, but with the current implementation the value of the field name is String &quot;null&quot; .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This happens only in the case of unmarshalling JSON to a subclass.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows XP,  JDK 1.6.0_14&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
